<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-762-694  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 762 694.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  Sept 25 1989 v10 n38 p35(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>As new industries come on-line, MIS hiring will boom.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Saks, Shirin.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Businesses in several diverse industries are expanding their useof computers, and new MIS career opportunities are expected toopen up as a result.andP;  Construction companies, agriculture-relatedbusinesses such as food processing companies, airline operations,and companies in the retail industry increasingly realize thevalue of computers for business applications, and need MIS staffto help them leverage technology.andP;  Companies in the financialservices arena, however, have scaled back their MIS hiring in thewake of concerns that linger from the Oct 1987 stock market crash.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     EmploymentMISTrendsBusiness.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>